# FI-APP Development Guidelines

## Component Structure
- Use Server/Client components appropriately
- Implement proper loading/error states
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Follow atomic design principles
- Implement responsive layouts for small and big screens

## State Management
- Use React Context for global state
- Server components for data fetching
- Form state with React Hook Form

## Types & Interfaces
- Create comprehensive type definitions for all entities
- Use zod for validation schemas
- Export types from a central location

## Best Practices
- Implement error boundaries
- Use React Suspense for loading states
- Optimize images and assets
- Write unit tests for critical functions
- Add accessibility features
- Do not use any as fixer